                <p class="about-long">You can call me Kayla. I am a curious soul, a mother, and a perpetual student. I have a degree in Psychology with a focus in Pre-Medicine. I worked in Mental Health as a Behavioral Technician for four years and was actively applying to Medical School until the birth of my first son and two weeks later the COVID pandemic put the whole world on pause. <br><br> During this time, I found myself questioning my entire career path and realized that I wanted a lifestyle that matched my talents in psychology and graphic design. I have worked as a freelance graphic designer and have always enjoyed it as a hobby. It wasn’t a serious endeavor until I discovered the world of UX Design. It felt as if my entire life’s experience aligned with this job description so here I am ready to turn your ideas into tangible designs!</p>
